column2: Table 2#8#4# Price Indexes for Personal Consumption Expenditures

column3: Personal consumption expenditures excluding food and energy \2\
Market-based personal consumption expenditures excluding food and energy \3\

column2: 1. Consists of gasoline and other energy goods and of electricity and gas.
2. Food consists of food and beverages purchased for off-premises consumption; food
services, which include purchased meals and beverages, are not classified as food.
3. This index is a supplemental measure that is based on household expenditures for
which there are observable price measures.  It excludes most implicit prices (for
example, financial services furnished without payment) and the final consumption
expenditures of nonprofit institutions serving households.
